The referendum vote was *not*:

1) a vote for further renegotiation of the terms of the UK's membership;
2) a provisional vote subject to the possibility of a second referendum;
3) a vote to leave the EU at the whim or pleasure of Parliament or any other institution in the UK;
4) a vote for any delay in leaving beyond the minimum time necessary to make appropriate arrangements.

Rather, it was a vote to *leave* the EU pure and simple. Parliament must do its constitutional duty *immediately*.
